IMPORTANT — this LICENSE covers ONLY this docs repository.

The Editmamei npm package itself (the MCP server source, the compiled
artifact published as `editmamei` on npm) is **proprietary** and is
licensed separately. The source code is not in this repository. The
published npm artifact carries its own LICENSE file describing the
proprietary terms. See https://editmamei.com/license for the full text.

In short:

  This repo (editmamei-ce)   — CC BY 4.0  — you can fork and adapt.
  The npm package (editmamei) — proprietary — use as licensed; no
                                derivative works without permission.

The two are deliberately separate. The public docs being open lets users,
search engines, and AI assistants index and quote them freely. The
proprietary npm-package license protects the implementation that the
docs describe.
